WEBVTT

00:00.409 --> 00:02.130
Do you know what Fritz

00:02.131 --> 00:03.165
<i>has been working on?</i>

00:03.166 --> 00:06.367
(coughing, shouting)

00:06.368 --> 00:08.544
<i>He's responsible for
thousands of deaths.</i>

00:08.545 --> 00:09.989
You may have changed your religion,

00:09.990 --> 00:10.985
but don't think for a second

00:10.986 --> 00:12.247
you can change your heritage.

00:12.248 --> 00:15.002
But if the worst disputes
between warring nations

00:15.003 --> 00:18.052
<i>can be resolved, can't two
old friends make peace?</i>

00:18.053 --> 00:20.901
I would like you to meet my
good friend, Dr. Niels Bohr.

00:20.902 --> 00:23.256
Are you familiar with Heisenberg's
uncertainty principle?

00:23.257 --> 00:24.657
<i>What about Margot and Ilse?</i>

00:24.658 --> 00:26.530
ELSA: <i>They're determined
to make their lives here.</i>

00:26.531 --> 00:28.929
Perhaps they'll change their
minds once they see how happy

00:28.930 --> 00:30.589
<i>a person can be in New Jersey.</i>

00:30.590 --> 00:32.762
I am conducting this
inquiry at the request

00:32.764 --> 00:35.032
<i>- of Mr. J. Edgar Hoover.</i>
- EINSTEIN: <i>Hoover?</i>

00:35.033 --> 00:36.601
What does he want with me?

00:36.602 --> 00:38.169
SECRETARY: <i>Dr. Lenard, it's an honor.</i>

00:38.170 --> 00:39.169
<i>He's expecting you, sir.</i>

00:39.170 --> 00:41.105
<i>Heil, mein Fuhrer!</i>

00:41.106 --> 00:42.975
Welcome to the Nazi Party, Dr. Lenard.

